title: Change the name or gender on your driving licence

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
chunks.html_content: Send DVLA your old driving licence along with the right application form and any supporting documents to change your name or gender.
chunks.plain_content:
Change the name or gender on your driving licence
Send DVLA your old driving licence along with the right application form and any supporting documents to change your name or gender.

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
chunks.html_content:
The process is the same if you want to change your title, for example from Ms to Dr. You do not need to send evidence unless its a hereditary title.

Youll get a new licence. You can still drive while you wait for your new licence.

It does not cost anything to change your name or gender on your driving licence.

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
Fill in the application form
chunks.html_content:
Theres a different process in Northern Ireland.

Fill in:

  • form D1 Application for a driving licence if you have a car or motorbike licence
  • form D2 Application for a lorry/bus licence if you have a lorry or bus licence

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
Fill in the application form
chunks.html_content:
Send your completed form to DVLA with:

  • your photocard or paper driving licence
  • any original documents that confirm your new name or gender

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
If you have a paper driving licence
chunks.plain_content:
Change the name or gender on your driving licence
If you have a paper driving licence
You must send a recent passport-style photo.

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
If you want to change your photo at the same time
chunks.html_content:
You need to send:

  • a recent passport-style photo
  • a cheque or postal order for 17, payable to DVLA (theres no fee if youre over 70 or have a medical short period licence)

Damaged or altered cheques will not be accepted.

heading_context: Change the name or gender on your driving licence
If you cannot send your old driving licence
chunks.html_content:
You can still apply if your old licence has been lost, stolen or destroyed. Youll have to say what happened to it when you fill in the form. Include a cheque or postal order for 20, payable to DVLA.

Damaged or altered cheques will not be accepted.
